Nothing you use are doing great!

You did a wonderful job. I received a response very promptly and problem solved right away.
Made a certain item more specific or give a choice to purchase both. I'm honestly not sure if the problem can be resolved.

I wasn't the customer service they were just the messenger- I feel disappointing that I can't have a large (expensive!) order shipped to home. My child is too young to bring it home on her own. I realized after ordering that it was going to her school. It is likely that parts of the order will be lost or at least cause a lot of unnecessary trouble.
You listened and you responded, in a thoughtful impactful manner.
I had a problem with my order and Karen was able to cancel that order for me and then I was able to re-order.  She was great!
Everything is great.. one item I wanted to order sold out, but I was very surprised how fast it was restocked.

I complained that the paper envelope used to ship my order soaked through and I recommended poly mailers. The response was sort of "not our problem, contact Shutterfly Customer Service" without even a direct link to the proper Shutterfly address.  At Shutterfly I could Not find a place to comment about order problems, only a generic satisfaction site like this page.  I was fobbed-off by both Scholastic and Shutterfly. I think I rescued the envelope sufficiently quickly to prevent photo damage.
I usually make about 3 scholastic book orders a year, and I have never had a problem.  This was the first time, and it was corrected immediately.  Thank you!

The short directions given took me to a page that did not work. I am taking over a position from last year as the librarian at St. William School.  The person I am replacing said we have a $900 balance in our account that I can use but I have not been able to get into the system to check or to order from the account.  Thank you.
offer dollar books offer dollar books for teachers
WHY am I constantly having issues with logging into my account this year?  It's taken TWO representatives and customer service email to help. NOW, I am unable to log in again. WHY????

You can learn to rectify a lost package better. You all lost our package during covid.  You wouldn't handle the situation and sent me to UPS which was a nightmare.  They never rectified over 300 dollars of lost books and my school families were very upset. I almost didn't return to your business. Not one customer service agent could help me all because you outsource your product for shipping and ultimately that's passing the buck! You never reimbursed my school families for lost merchandise two school years ago.

Your representative told me that my account was set up as a parent account not an educator account for my classroom. They offered to fix the account for me, but did not follow through. My account is still a parent account, and I cannot set up a class or have a teacher page. It was helpful to know that theres something wrong. BUT it would be more helpful to actually have it fixed. Why do you order books for me. I wanted to order more books and you sent the books to me before I could finish ordering. I do not understand why you ship books out when I did not finish my order. Also you need value books at 1.00 for families to order. I have families that do not order because they say it is too expensive.

Wishing there was contact information that would get directly to those making the decisions/changes in lieu of going through representatives. A few changes I am struggling withthe lack of some tech options in the bonus catalog and also the automatic order deadlines.

Wishing there was contact information that would get directly to those making the decisions/changes in lieu of going through representatives. A few changes I am struggling withthe lack of some tech options in the bonus catalog and also the automatic order deadlines.
I was delivered a wrong order. It was corrected quickly and the parent is happy for complete order. Thank you.

Your response was immediate, and I appreciate that.  I neglected to see that you set that due dates.  That was my fault.  But I'm disappointed that I don't have more control over that based on what works for my classroom.  Now I will end up having to pay shipping for the ones that are left to send in. The points I earn will also be affected with 2 smaller orders that were processed separately.
I received a response within 30 minutes!  This was great as I didn't have to worry about what I was going to tell this particular parent regarding the missing item.
I appreciate the timely response to my question. Your customer service team is always very supportive and easy to work with. I appreciate it.
It doesn't seem like the rep read my question carefully.
Why did you get rid of Club Leo? Please make a flyer or group with a special name for Spanish or bilingual books. I want to promote the books in my dual school.
Improved wait time. Have teacher site and book clubs have the same representatives.
I was looking for the book Persepolis by Marjane Satrapi and you don't stock it.  It is a very popular book for 8th graders and very surprising & disappointing that you don't carry it.

I am discouraged by the new policy of setting due dates based upon what works for Scholastic, and not the teacher.  I have used Scholastic for 25 years in my teaching career and never had an issue until now.  I may be looking for other book orders to replace Scholastic based upon the new changes.
Books should be able to be sent to teachers house. Makes life easier with a large district like ours.

I contacted customer service to find out how to purchase book coupons for my students.  For many years. I've used them as gifts for my class.  My dissatisfaction is that these have been discontinued.  These are things I would have purchased  this month.  As no parents placed orders, I will wait to purchase any books for my class until November.

I do not care for the new format of your ordering. Really, I was super sad that you didn't offer the 12 reads of Christmas books this year. I've bought them every year for my grandkids and we look forward to the tradition of reading a book a night.

The changes in the way rewards work and not being aware that a cart is going through before it goes through is frustrating. I preferred the old reward system and would prefer that book orders be put through at the end of the month instead of in the middle since the magazines usually go out at the start of the month.
send me the paper forms when I have requested a month ago I don't have time
My concern was addressed immediately and easily. Thank you!

Teachers aren't/weren't aware that parents are actually charged til we close out the order. If an item a parent ordered is not available, they or the teacher (w/parent approval) should be able to substitute a cost similar item (parent gave me permission). I wound up using my point to get a replacement book for the student as it was the weekend and I couldn't reach anyone and needed to place the order. Having flexibility and options would be great.
I was told my order got delivered on Friday, but really it was delivered today.  It took a long time.  I also don't like that I have to pay shipping if I don't have a $25 order.
I appreciate that it was resolved the same day I contacted Scholastic.
I would like to be able to use my bonus points whenever I need to and not have to pay shipping.

I have had my school order delivered to my home for years, even before the pandemic, but was told this is no longer possible. I am the director of a half-day preschool. We are housed at a church and there are multiple buildings on the campus. I can't have any orders from any vendor delivered here because the usps, amazon, fed ex, and ups will leave packages at all hours, often at the wrong building,  and often near the street. There is no one here to sign for packages from 1pm on. I think Scholastic has outgrown us.
I would have called, but I couldn't find a phone number - I used the chat feature.
The representatives reached out quickly and replied promptly. I'm very pleased with the quality of their customer service.
not so many questions and simplify the questonnaire Make the form available with po for new customers
Nothing!  Janet was very helpful and pointed me in the right direction to find my lost book box.
The help in figuring out who had ordered was great but it would be nice to have more information on the packing slip or at least available online to look up if needed.

The email I received stating a coupon of $10.00 off $25.00 would automatically be added to my order was very deceiving. There was not $10.00 deducted from my total, but I could spend $10.00 additionally without charge if I had an order of $25.00. As a teacher, I would much rather have $10.00 taken off of my order than being able to spend an additional $10.00 of individual books from a list. I was trying to order a class set of books for students as a Christmas gift and ended up canceling my order because of how it was worded in the email verse how the actual coupon worked. I was very disappointed in how this was worded and how the person I chatted with responded to my concern.

I have been ordering Scholastic for 36 years. Students get very excited about seeing the flyers and receiving the books they've ordered. Not taking mail-in orders or me being able to call in book orders will affect many students in my classroom. Many do not have computer access.  I also feel changing the flyers that are sent home wiIl also decrease the amount of book orders that are placed.  Seeing the books, at their reading level visually is important. I just wanted to voice my concern as I have many disappointed students who will not be ordering books.

1.  Your new system of parents making a book order online did not take into consideration parents who do not have access to technology nor a credit card to make an online order.  I believe options to parents on how to order books for their child is key to increase book orders.  Offer the option of parents filling out the book order on the book order form and teacher inputting order. 2.  Teacher orders of $25 + to receive the $10 to buy extra books for classroom should go back to the way it was.  Monthly!!!  Not this 4 week promotion cycle that does not make sense and teacher has to order by a deadline.  Make it, make sense!!! 3.  I was a gold apple teacher last year, this year not even close.   The book orders did not make sense and parents were looking for a page to mark their order.  First year, I didn't come close to the $300+ of book orders I get yearly.    4.  I say it every year,  your collection of Spanish literature needs to improve and provide a variety of choices.  Club Leo needs to be offered in a monthly book order, just like the English books.  5.  I love Scholastic!  I have been buying your books since I was in  Kindergarten at .25 cents for a Mercer Mayer book. (By the way, I still have those books).  You provided choices for kids like me who was raised by a single mother to feel like she had access to ordering books just like the other kids.     Offer your dollar books for some of our children whose parents do not have the means to purchase the books at current prices. I have a problem with not allowing students to order the old way.  You are having parents order online.  I don't care for this process. (computers, TV's, radios, etc.)

Many teachers are not happy that you no longer offer $1 books each month. The $1 books gave us the opportunity to purchase books for our students as Christmas gifts. You also no longer have the quality of flyers available to purchase from and prices have gone up. As a result, my parents are not purchasing books this year. It was stated that prices had to increase due to the economy. When you work in a school that has lower income students, they won't ever be able to afford these books. As a result, I do not have enough points to purchase the bundles of books you offer to teachers because of the price and limited selection. Very disappointed in the route you have taken this year.

The woman I spoke to said that she could send me flyers the next week instead of the week I asked for them. I wanted it to be right away. I requested that flyers for Holiday books (for November) be sent to me. They have not been sent to me yet.
Offer more $2 options around holiday time like previous years.  Not just one a month.

Checkout is too difficult. When I go to checkout I never see the opportunities that were offered me. For example, this past order, I was promised $10 off with an order of $25 or more spent. When I went to checkout I could not figure out how to do it. I never did get that discount. Check the comments above.

I do not believe that it is clear that the automated dates for shipping of the clubs are set by scholastic. It leaves the teacher, no flexibility in their scheduling. I would like to change the dates that the auto ship occurs on and that the orders are placed. I am looking at other options outside of scholastic, for this reason for next school year for our families.
Thank you for all you do!

Im trying to find out if the $2 book is a weekly thing or monthly. This wasnt answered in my email I was disappointed to hear that the Judy Newman $1 book was canceled. I was then told you have a $2 book. I asked if this is weekly or monthly and no one has answered this. I also wish it was easier to find the $2 book

The young lady That assisted did an amazing job. My order auto sent , but I had not added my teacher order and did not know that would happen. She helped me add my order and made one very happy customer.

Given screenshots of where to find the things I was looking for on the website

The person i spoke to was very helpful.

My apologies for having an outstanding invoice.  After repeated attempts to contact someone within the credit and collections department, I called the customer service department.  The customer service rep seemed a little annoyed that I didn't know my customer ID number, but she eventually figured it out.  It turned out that the invoice wasn't attached to that number anyway.  Eventually, someone recommended that I mail a check to the credit and collections department.  Unfortunately, I am not able to pay via check.  I submitted a credit card payment, but I am still waiting for the credit and collections department to tell me whether or not they were able to connect that payment to the invoice.  Needless to say, I really wish that my original credit card payment had been processed when I first ordered the books.  I hope that everything is resolved soon.

Communicate the entire overhaul of scholastic clubs clearly to teachers before the school year started. Stop changing the website layout so that as soon as I know how to find something its somewhere else. And communicate with teachers about the major changes to your program. Your new system was not communicated to teachers. Your features are hidden on the website.

My exact questions were not answered. I refused a very form response. The parents of my students dont read English, dont always have phones they can use for the QR code, dont trust apps and corporations or have credit and debit cards. They want to fill out a form and give me cash so their children can order books. I would like to know why this cant be an option? Also, if I take it upon myself to submit all orders under my teacher account, will I still earn bonus points?  Im sure the new QR code method is great for other school populations, but it is also very limiting for others.
Maybe have all the information on one web page instead of multiple?

Customer service was excellent. Extremely disappointed in the removal of the dollar store when us teachers work so hard to promote your books. Again, I am extremely disappointed in the changes and scholastic over the past several years. We used to have opportunities for dollar books. Then students had to spend more than $100 to open the dollar bookstore. Neither of them are available. It is a shame when parents spend all of this money and teachers get some rewards but not, something as simple as a dollar book.

My parent's book orders were submitted before they date that I told them, so your company individually submitted the orders. Therefore, I received very few bonus points...again. I will not be doing any more orders with your company.
Looking forward to a long relationship.

I tried to change the school address. We are part of the Mundelein Park District and our building is only open for limited hours each day. I wanted to change the address to the main building at 1401 Midlothian Rd.

The new policy of automatic order submissions does not really work for me.  I typically check to see how many orders we have then send out a reminder to parents.  The I order books to get us up to the next bonus point level.  With the automatic submission, I didn't get a chance to do any of that, and because of it we only had 2 books in this last order, and none of our classrooms added their their classroom library this month.  I was disappointed. I was told the automatic submission is the new procedure.  I will try to stay on top of the online order dates that are preset so this does not happen again.

A lot has changed with the automatic processing of orders that I was unaware of which made us lose out of the $10 free books earned. There seems to be many changes in your selection as well particularly with the $1-$2 books and being able to choose a selection of those books once an order reaches a certain dollar amount.

The interaction is fine. The new way to order is not. Melissa did her best to answer my questions and look for solutions. This method is just not a very practical one for our families in my opinion but I will try it.

The customer service aspect was fine.  I was asking about some updates to the system that have changed that there is not an option to opt out of.  That part has nothing to do with the customer service piece itself.
I still have not received flyers for Kindergarten. I need flyers for kindergarteners.
I am always so impressed with your customer service! You understand teachers are busy and are so helpful!!
Give an order due window that coincides with the date to receive for holiday delivery (halloween due 10/10, Thanksgiving due 11/5 so delivery will be before each of the holidays. Described above.

The email I received stated $10 off an order of $25 or more. I got the promotion of $10 in free books.  That's not $10 off.  I polled the teaching staff and 100% agreed - a promotion of $10 in free books is very different than $10 off.  I have been ordering books from Scholastic for over 30 years and never misunderstood the promotional offerings.

I am very concerned about the separating or siloing of any books that do not contain a white, hetero-cis perspective.  I perceive this as deeply damaging to all students and communities.  I am deeply disappointed that Scholastic ever moved even a bit close to this decision, let alone implemented it across the board with little or no communication. The books offered at a book fair or catalog should represent all Americans, not just a select group.  No books should be siloed as 'diverse'.  As many positive perspectives as possible, particularly the identities of all children, should be included as a matter of course.
I was pleased with the quick response!

I talked to the rep about bonus points.  I had been saving for years for a MacBook for my classroom.  I am so close to having the amount of bonus points that were needed, and now, without warning, you've discontinued offering it.  I can't tell you how heart-broken I am.  My classroom really could have used a new MacBook, and I sacrified for years to be able to save up enough for it.  So, so disappointed.
I do not like having to call in for student orders! I have talked to a lot of teachers that are done with scholastic because of this change.

The customer service person who responded was fine. They responded promptly and with accurate info. My disappointment is in the severe reduction of your online-only offerings for high school students. Just a few months ago, I would scroll for pages and pages to look at books. Now the list is ridiculously short, and I don't see any reason to continue working with Scholastic anymore if my demographic (10th-12th graders) are not going to be serviced anymore. You got rid of Teen book club, and now the online offerings are drastically limited.

I received the "Your questions has been received" email, but have not received a response on steps to resolve my issue. I find it odd that you sent a feedback form asking about the customer service I received BEFORE giving me customer service. I have not received a suggestion to resolve the problem. What you can do is just send the book I ordered. That would be great!
make it easier to create an account for a library

I wish the rep would have been able to answer questions asked and provided more details. I would have liked to use my teacher points for ipad, min fridge, etc for my classroom.  There were none available at this time and the rep said that she was unaware of when they will be back in stock.  I asked if I could get notified when they were and she said that they change every month and cant provide that information.

Keep up with the good customer service. You are always prompt in solving problems and I always appreciate it! I'd say it Scholastic is one of the best customer services experiences I have ever had. Thank you!

I am just disappointed that the way Scholastic changed the book ordering due date had no solution, it was changed and there is no fix. Scholastic has made a required book order date that a teacher does not have the right to change.  This makes no sense.  It should be a choice for a teacher.  And for some weird reason you put the date at the middle of the month and we always make ours due near the end of the month, so now you are completing orders in the middle of our order separating up my points so I don't get as many as I usually would.  I think this should be a choice.

I am very disappointed that you have taken away the ability to set my own due dates. You are submitting orders on the teachers behalf and that means that sometimes an order is placed before I am able to add my own teacher order for the class. I cannot use my bonus points and need to wait and do not get to take advantage of your monthly bonus '. I am extremely disappointed in scholastic this year. May not be worth it for me to continue. You have also reduced the amount of dollar books we can order for our classes.

I have been a Scholastic member for over 30 years, but I do not plan on using it on a regular basis any more. I only used it this time because I had a student whose parent, on her own, searched the site and submitted an order to me. I did not pass out any catalogues or tell students about ordering. Bring back the good literature instead of just the books based on movies or video games. Bring back the $1 books.

Not crazy about this new format that I cannot choose my own due dates and shipping dates for my classroom.  In the past, I handed out orders, gave parents one week to order and placed my order WITH parent orders.  I could count on when books would arrive for families.  I also sent them EVERY month - orders are now much fewer and closer together (November and Holiday) are very close together.
